{
  "comment": [
    "Shared enroll-link vectors — core EnrollLink.kt (EnrollLinkVectorTest) and web/src/enroll/enrolllink.ts (enrolllink.test.ts) MUST agree on every row; a divergence is a vector failure.",
    "Link shape: <origin>/enroll#a1.<b64url-nopad({\"v\":1,\"o\":..,\"t\":..,\"e\":..})>. parse() is TOTAL: null on any malformed input, never throws.",
    "Normalization pins: strip ASCII whitespace [ \\t\\n\\r\\v\\f] from the b64 body, then trailing '=', so padded/chat-wrapped links parse on all clients (rows *-accepted).",
    "Decision pins: UNKNOWN extra keys are ACCEPTED (forward compat; kotlin twin uses ignoreUnknownKeys=true to match JSON.parse). DUPLICATE top-level keys are REJECTED on both twins (shared lexical scan; a backslash escape inside a key also rejects, so \\u0074 cannot alias t). v compares NUMERICALLY (1.0 accepted — post-JSON.parse JS cannot distinguish 1.0 from 1; the string \"1\" is rejected). Decoded b64 must RE-ENCODE to the normalized body (canonical-form pin, masks decoder leniency). Total input length capped at 8192 (boundary row is exactly 8192 and accepted). Origins must be canonical lowercase http(s)://host[:port] — no path/slash/userinfo/uppercase; bracketed IPv6 allowed.",
    "compose pins: every composeRejects row {name,o,t,e} MUST make compose return null on both twins (ill-formed UTF-16 rejection). Lone surrogates are written as \\udXXX JSON escapes because raw lone surrogates are not valid UTF-8 (the file could not carry them literally); both loaders pass the escapes through unpaired. Well-formed astral input (4-byte UTF-8 emoji) is pinned ACCEPTING via the emoji roundTrips rows and the astral parse row."
  ],
